    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce new funding and requirements for provision of segregated cycle paths",
        "additional_details": "To improve and open up new cycle ways. To improve conditions and safety for cyclists and for drivers of motor vehicles. To promote cycling as a green transport alternative. To help our target of net zero carbon emissions.",
        "background": "Any new roads being built should be legally required to have provision for a cycle path, segregated from motor traffic. Furthermore, the Government should provide funding to retrofit segregated cycle lanes onto the existing infrastructure.",
